parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, indicating a potential safety risk, and may lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of an accident, putting the driver and passengers at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: or flashes; the airbag system malfunctions; the driver's side airbag module fails; the passenger side airbag light comes on; the airbag light comes on and off randomly; the airbag system is inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed acceleration and hesitation can cause accidents or near-misses, especially when merging onto highways or intersections, and can lead to rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or delays accelerating when pressing the gas pedal
especially when stopping at red lights or stop signs
and may suddenly accelerate rapidly afterwards.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch and transmission issues can cause the vehicle to hesitate or stall, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle hesitates or stalls when shifting gears
and the gear shift may lock or become stuck in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical and infotainment system issues can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The dashboard lights and warning messages are malfunctioning
the collision light shows up on the dash
and the remote start and door lock functions are not working properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The safety recalls and odometer tampering can lead to accidents or near-misses due to unknown or unaddressed safety issues.
symptoms: The vehicle has an active recall for the hood latch
and the odometer reading is suspected to be tampered with.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake and rotor issues can cause accidents or loss of control due to reduced stopping power.
symptoms: The brake pads need to be replaced prematurely
and the rotors are warped or damaged.
